WEBVTT

00:00:01.080 --> 00:00:03.880
Time to put real credentials in a place forks cannot

00:00:03.880 --> 00:00:06.520
reach! We will set two secrets, prove they

00:00:06.520 --> 00:00:09.080
are write-only, then fork the repo and watch

00:00:09.080 --> 00:00:09.800
them disappear.

00:00:10.773 --> 00:00:13.493
Most teams drop a dot env file into the repo

00:00:13.493 --> 00:00:16.213
because it is the obvious move. The

00:00:16.213 --> 00:00:19.093
problem is the fork inherits a byte-for-byte

00:00:19.093 --> 00:00:21.893
copy of the image, so your sandbox boots

00:00:21.893 --> 00:00:24.613
with the production Stripe key and starts charging

00:00:24.613 --> 00:00:26.053
real customer cards.

00:00:29.444 --> 00:00:32.084
First we will set a secret in env mode

00:00:32.804 --> 00:00:35.444
. The value will land as an environment variable

00:00:35.524 --> 00:00:38.164
inside the container. Notice the empty

00:00:38.164 --> 00:00:40.884
current flag, we are declaring this

00:00:40.884 --> 00:00:43.684
is a brand new secret with no prior value.

00:00:44.690 --> 00:00:47.250
Set. The value will land in the container as

00:00:47.250 --> 00:00:48.610
an environment variable.

00:00:52.120 --> 00:00:54.680
Now a file mode secret. File mode never

00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:57.800
puts the value in the container environment. It

00:00:57.800 --> 00:01:02.120
writes it to a file at slash run slash secrets, using

00:01:02.120 --> 00:01:04.680
Docker standard mechanism. Prefer this

00:01:04.680 --> 00:01:05.880
for anything sensitive.

00:01:06.791 --> 00:01:09.351
Set as a file. The container reads

00:01:09.351 --> 00:01:12.071
it from /run/secrets

00:01:12.551 --> 00:01:13.751
, never as an env var.

00:01:17.238 --> 00:01:20.038
Let us list what we have. Names and modes

00:01:20.038 --> 00:01:22.598
only. The list never shows values

00:01:22.918 --> 00:01:24.198
, no matter who is asking.

00:01:27.317 --> 00:01:30.277
Names and modes only. Values

00:01:30.357 --> 00:01:31.717
are never displayed.

00:01:32.702 --> 00:01:35.342
The CLI follows the GitHub Actions model

00:01:35.902 --> 00:01:38.462
: get returns a digest, never the value

00:01:39.262 --> 00:01:41.822
. If you lose track of a secret, you do not

00:01:41.822 --> 00:01:44.542
peek, you rotate, and the audit log

00:01:44.542 --> 00:01:46.542
records it as a deliberate change.

00:01:49.934 --> 00:01:56.174
Now the part that surprises people. The secret get command returns a digest, not the value

00:01:56.654 --> 00:01:59.214
. There is no flag that gives the plaintext back

00:01:59.694 --> 00:02:02.734
. That is the GitHub Actions model: write only

00:02:02.734 --> 00:02:03.454
by design.

00:02:06.648 --> 00:02:09.448
Digest, not plaintext. The CLI

00:02:09.448 --> 00:02:11.208
won't show secrets to anyone.

00:02:14.601 --> 00:02:17.161
Lost the value? Do not peek

00:02:17.481 --> 00:02:20.441
. Rotate. The rotate-secret flag skips

00:02:20.441 --> 00:02:23.081
the precondition check, and the audit log marks

00:02:23.081 --> 00:02:25.641
the change as a deliberate rotation

00:02:26.201 --> 00:02:28.201
. Loud, intentional, safe.

00:02:29.115 --> 00:02:31.835
Rotated. The audit log marks this

00:02:31.835 --> 00:02:33.275
as a deliberate replacement.

00:02:34.206 --> 00:02:36.766
Here is the payoff. The fork shares the

00:02:36.766 --> 00:02:39.486
parent's encrypted data, but the secret

00:02:39.486 --> 00:02:42.046
store is scoped per repo, so the

00:02:42.046 --> 00:02:45.246
fork lists empty and cannot interpolate

00:02:45.326 --> 00:02:46.846
any of your production keys.

00:02:50.323 --> 00:02:53.363
Now the punchline. We will fork the repo. The

00:02:53.363 --> 00:02:55.923
fork is a byte-for-byte copy of the parent

00:02:55.923 --> 00:02:56.803
encrypted image.

00:02:59.760 --> 00:03:02.320
Fork created. A byte-for-byte copy of the

00:03:02.320 --> 00:03:03.200
encrypted image.

00:03:06.625 --> 00:03:09.505
But when we list the fork secrets: empty

00:03:09.985 --> 00:03:13.425
. No Stripe key, no database password, no API token. The fork canno

00:03:15.825 --> 00:03:18.385
t pretend to be you. That is why clone

00:03:18.385 --> 00:03:21.265
production, break nothing actually works.

00:03:24.384 --> 00:03:27.104
Empty. The fork starts with no secrets, by

00:03:27.104 --> 00:03:27.584
design.

00:03:29.231 --> 00:03:31.871
And that is secrets locked down where forks

00:03:31.871 --> 00:03:34.511
cannot follow. See you in the next one!
